# Code owners for DreamLayer's security-critical, self-guarding files.
#
# gitleaks scans the config from a PR's own head and honours inline
# `# gitleaks:allow`, so a contributor could weaken the secret-scan gate in the
# same PR that introduces a secret (refute 2026-07-18). The scanners, their
# allowlists, and the privacy guardrails are exactly the files whose weakening
# must be a deliberate, reviewed act — so they route to a human owner here.
# This is advisory until branch protection enables "Require review from Code
# Owners" for these paths; enabling it is the recommended companion setting.

# Secret-scan gate + its allowlist
/.gitleaks.toml            @LetsGetToWorkBro
# SAST rules + custom privacy rules
/.semgrep/                 @LetsGetToWorkBro
# Supply-chain / dependency policy
/reality-core/deny.toml    @LetsGetToWorkBro
# All CI workflows (the gates themselves)
/.github/workflows/        @LetsGetToWorkBro
# This ownership file
/.github/CODEOWNERS        @LetsGetToWorkBro

# The runtime privacy guardrails — the "never identify a stranger" defence.
/host-python/src/dreamlayer/object_lens/person_guard.py   @LetsGetToWorkBro
/host-python/src/dreamlayer/object_lens/recognizer.py     @LetsGetToWorkBro
